## âš¡ Essential Terminal Commands

### File Operations

```
pwd        â†’ show current directory
ls         â†’ list files
cd         â†’ change directory
mkdir      â†’ create folder
rm         â†’ delete file
cp         â†’ copy file
mv         â†’ move/rename file
```

---

### Reading Files

```
cat file.txt
less file.txt
head file.txt
tail file.txt
```

These are heavily used in log analysis.

---

### Permission System

```
ls -l
chmod 755 file
chown user file
sudo command
```

Linux security is built around permissions.

---

### User Information

```
whoami
id
groups
sudo -l
```

Critical for understanding privilege escalation.

---

### Process Monitoring

```
ps aux
top
htop
kill <pid>
```

Seeing what runs on a system is a key security skill.

---

### Networking Commands

```
ip a
ping <ip>
netstat -tulnp
ss -tulnp
tcpdump
```

You cannot understand hacking without networking.

